setThreadLocalConnection

public static void setThreadLocalConnection(Connection connection)
Sets the connection of the ThreadLocal variable of ThreadLocalConnectionStrategy.
This can be useful in cases where the core system running in the current deployment is not a Bo2 system, but a JDBC based system that can only use the JDBC connection transaction mechanism. In such a deployment the Bo2 modules can share the JDBC connection of the core system using a ThreadLocalConnectionStrategy. This means that the connectionStrategy property in the manager's properties file should have be set to ThreadLocalConnectionStrategy. In such a case, the close() method of the provider should not be called. The core module that uses the Bo2 operation should close the resources and commit the transactions explicitly. In this case the Bo2 deployment should not use any transaction manager; the transaction should be coordinated by the calling module.
In a case like this, it would be preferable first to create the Provider and let him coordinate the transaction and provide the JDBC connection to the core module.

Parameters:
connection - JDBC connection to set.

getDeployment

public static Bo2Deployment getDeployment(String path)
Gets the Bo2Deployment that is defined in the properties file found in the specified resource path.

Parameters:
path - Path to the resource file that contains the deployment properties.
Returns:
Returns the Bo2Deployment object that was created using the properties file found in the specified path. If the creation of the Bo2Deployment file fails, then a RuntimeException is thrown.

getProvider

public static Provider getProvider()
                            throws InitializationException
Gets a new provider, created by the default Bo2Deployment. This method delegates to Bo2Deployment.getProvider() which always creates a new Provider.

Returns:
Returns a new provider, created by the Bo2Deployment that has been marked as default.
Throws:
InitializationException - If the creation of the Provider fails.
